67-1808. POWERS AND DUTIES OF THE COMMITTEE. The committee shall have the following powers and duties:

(1) To meet not less than two (2) times each year;

(2) To establish rules for governance and operation of committee proceedings;

(3) To request applications for funding from the Idaho millennium income fund;

(4) To meet to hear testimony and to consider applications for funding from the Idaho millennium income fund;

(5) To evaluate the actual and potential success of programs funded with moneys from the Idaho millennium income fund; and

(6) To present recommendations annually to the legislature for the use of the moneys in the Idaho millennium income fund.

[(67-1808) 67-1805, added 2002, ch. 352, sec. 3, p. 1006; am. and redesig. 2006, ch. 187, sec. 8, p. 590.]
